Detailed Description

cvmx_bgx::_spu::_an_xnp_tx

Software programs this register with the contents of the AN message next page or unformatted next page link code word to be transmitted during autonegotiation. Next page exchange occurs after the base link code words have been exchanged if either end of the link segment sets the NP bit to 1, indicating that it has at least one next page to send. Once initiated, next page exchange continues until both ends of the link segment set their NP bits to 0. See section 802.3 section 73.7.7 for details.
